  <section class="py-20 bg-surface-dim" aria-labelledby="faq-heading">
    <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8">
      <h2 id="faq-heading" class="font-display text-4xl sm:text-5xl font-800 text-ink tracking-wide uppercase mb-10">
        Frequently Asked <span class="text-accent">Questions</span>
      </h2>
      <div class="space-y-4">
        <details class="group border border-border bg-surface p-6 open:pb-8" open>
          <summary class="font-display text-xl font-bold uppercase tracking-wider text-ink cursor-pointer list-none flex items-center justify-between group-open:mb-4">
            What is a cleanroom conveyor?
            <svg class="w-6 h-6 text-ink-muted group-open:rotate-180 transition-transform flex-shrink-0 ml-4" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24"><path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M19 9l-7 7-7-7" /></svg>
          </summary>
          <div class="text-ink-muted leading-relaxed space-y-3">
            <p>A conveyor designed to operate within ISO 14644-1 classified environments without generating particles that compromise the cleanroom rating. Uses smooth, non-shedding surfaces (electropolished SS, anodized aluminum), sealed bearings, enclosed drives, and non-outgassing materials. Serves <a href="/industries/pharmaceutical-conveyors/" class="text-accent hover:text-accent-hover font-semibold">pharmaceutical</a>, medical device, and semiconductor manufacturing.</p>
          </div>
        </details>
        <details class="group border border-border bg-surface p-6 open:pb-8">
          <summary class="font-display text-xl font-bold uppercase tracking-wider text-ink cursor-pointer list-none flex items-center justify-between group-open:mb-4">
            What ISO classes require specialized conveyors?
            <svg class="w-6 h-6 text-ink-muted group-open:rotate-180 transition-transform flex-shrink-0 ml-4" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24"><path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M19 9l-7 7-7-7" /></svg>
          </summary>
          <div class="text-ink-muted leading-relaxed space-y-3">
            <p>ISO 7-8 use standard stainless steel with sealed bearings. ISO 6 requires enclosed drives and particle-tested belts. ISO 5 requires fully enclosed systems, HEPA-filtered enclosures, certified materials, and often through-wall drive placement to keep particle sources outside the classified zone.</p>
          </div>
        </details>
        <details class="group border border-border bg-surface p-6 open:pb-8">
          <summary class="font-display text-xl font-bold uppercase tracking-wider text-ink cursor-pointer list-none flex items-center justify-between group-open:mb-4">
            What belt materials are cleanroom compatible?
            <svg class="w-6 h-6 text-ink-muted group-open:rotate-180 transition-transform flex-shrink-0 ml-4" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24"><path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M19 9l-7 7-7-7" /></svg>
          </summary>
          <div class="text-ink-muted leading-relaxed space-y-3">
            <p>Silicone-free polyurethane (most common), PTFE-coated fiberglass, monofilament polyester mesh, and stainless steel flat wire. These generate minimal particles, do not outgas VOCs, and resist IPA and hydrogen peroxide cleaning. Standard PVC and rubber belts are not cleanroom-compatible.</p>
          </div>
        </details>
        <details class="group border border-border bg-surface p-6 open:pb-8">
          <summary class="font-display text-xl font-bold uppercase tracking-wider text-ink cursor-pointer list-none flex items-center justify-between group-open:mb-4">
            How do you validate a cleanroom conveyor?
            <svg class="w-6 h-6 text-ink-muted group-open:rotate-180 transition-transform flex-shrink-0 ml-4" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24"><path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M19 9l-7 7-7-7" /></svg>
          </summary>
          <div class="text-ink-muted leading-relaxed space-y-3">
            <p>Validation includes particle generation testing (measuring airborne particles at the belt surface during operation), outgassing testing (VOC emissions), surface finish verification (Ra values), and operational qualification under production conditions. The conveyor must not cause the room to exceed its ISO classification during operation.</p>
          </div>
        </details>
      </div>
